DOCUMENT();       

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
           "parserPopUp.pl"
           );
       
TEXT(beginproblem()); # standard preamble to each problem.


$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$b = random(6,14,2);
$c = random(2,9,1);
$half = $b/2;
$half_sq = $half**2;
$half_neg = - $half;
$k = - $half_sq - $c;
$symm = "t=$half_neg";
$neg_k = -$k;

BEGIN_TEXT
Question 4:
$BR
$SPACE
$BR
Consider the quadratic equation \( \ v(t) = t^2 + $b t - $c \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
a) What are the coordinates of the vertex?  $SPACE $SPACE ( \{ ans_rule(10) \} , \{ ans_rule(10) \} ) (give EXACT coordinates, no approximations)
$BR $SPACE $BR
b) What is the axis of symmetry? \{ ans_rule(20) \} $BR
$BITALIC (Do not just enter a number as your answer.  Enter your answer in the form of an equation for a vertical line of symmetry). $EITALIC

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp( $half_neg ) );
ANS(num_cmp( $k ) );
ANS(equation_cmp($symm,vars=>['t','y','v']) );


SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$BR $SPACE $BR 
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$BR
To complete the square, we take one half of the coefficient of $BITALIC t $EITALIC and square the result. This gives $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \left( \frac{1}{2} \cdot $b \right)^2  = $half_sq \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
Using this number, we can rewrite the formula for \( \ v(t) \) : $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ v(t) = \left( t^2+ $b t+ $half_sq \right) - $half_sq - $c \) $BR
\( \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ \ = \left( t + $half \right)^2 - $neg_k \)
$BR $SPACE $BR
Thus, the vertex of $BITALIC v $EITALIC is ( $half_neg , $k ), and the axis of symmetry is the vertical line \( \ t=$half_neg \) through the vertex.

$BR
END_SOLUTION

      
ENDDOCUMENT();  